  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Soak the&nbsp;<strong>rice noodles</strong>&nbsp;in&nbsp;<strong>cold water</strong>&nbsp;and set them aside to soften&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Peel and grate the <strong>brown</strong>&nbsp;<strong>onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>ginger</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-pork-meatball-and-mushroom-ramen/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the&nbsp;<strong>pork mince</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong>, <strong>grated ginger</strong>, <strong>onion</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> to a bowl&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Knead thoroughly with clean hands for 2-3 min, then shape&nbsp;into 10&nbsp;<span class=\"text-danger\">[20]&nbsp;</span><strong>meatballs</strong></p>\r\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid with a drizzle of<strong>&nbsp;vegetable oil&nbsp;</strong>over a medium heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the&nbsp;<strong>meatballs</strong> and cook 6-8 min, turning occasionally&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-pork-meatball-and-mushroom-ramen/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, tear the <strong>chestnut</strong>&nbsp;<strong>mushrooms</strong>&nbsp;into bite-sized pieces&nbsp;(this saves time and creates an interesting texture)</p>\r\n<p>Trim, then slice the <strong>spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> finely</p>\r\n<p>Slice the <strong>sugar snap peas</strong> in half lengthways</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-pork-meatball-and-mushroom-ramen/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained noodles</strong> to a pot and cover with plenty of<strong> boiled water</strong> and cook over a high heat for 4-7 min or until tender</p>\r\n<p>Re-boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-pork-meatball-and-mushroom-ramen/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, once the <strong>meatballs</strong>&nbsp;have browned, push them to one side of the pan and add the <strong>torn mushrooms</strong> to the other side and cook for 3 min or until crisp&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once the <strong>mushrooms</strong> are crisp and the <strong>meatballs</strong> are cooked through, add 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span><strong>&nbsp;soy sauce sachets</strong>&nbsp;to the <strong>mushrooms</strong> and cook for 1 min further</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-pork-meatball-and-mushroom-ramen/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, once the <strong>noodles</strong> are tender, add the<strong> sliced sugar snap peas</strong> to the pot and cook for 1 min further&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Drain the <strong>noodles&nbsp;</strong>and <strong>sugar snap peas</strong> and reserve the pot for the next step&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-pork-meatball-and-mushroom-ramen/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pot (no need to rinse it!) to a high heat&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Add the&nbsp;<strong>chipotle paste</strong>,<strong>&nbsp;chicken stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>, <strong>star anise</strong>, <strong>toasted sesame oil</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>remaining soy sauce</strong>, 1 tsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and 600ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [1.1l]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> to the pot, bring to the boil and cook for 1-2 min &ndash; this is your <strong>ramen broth&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-pork-meatball-and-mushroom-ramen/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, divide the <strong>noodles</strong> and <strong>sugar snaps peas</strong>&nbsp;into bowls</p>\r\n<p>Top the <strong>noodles </strong>and<strong> sugar snap peas</strong> with the <strong>fried mushrooms</strong> and <strong>meatballs</strong></p>\r\n<p>Pour the<strong> hot ramen broth</strong> over the noodles and garnish with the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>spring</strong> <strong>onion</strong> and <strong>toasted sesame seeds</strong> and enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
